One of us shouted before the other, but it didn't matter who was first.[r]
Our voices melted away into the same air. Intertwined in the same sky.[l][r]
I couldn't help but start blinking as my vision blurred, and the girl before me became nothing but a spot of color amidst the grey.[r]
Oh, come on! Don't get in the way, not now![l][r]
Stop it, tears! Come on, smile![l][r]
[r]My legs wouldn't budge. It felt like they froze solid, entrapped a prison of ice and snow.[l][r]
But I didn't feel cold. Even though I wasn't wearing my old parka, or my rugged boots, the cold and chill didn't reach me.[l][r]
Yuu ran towards me as I stood there like a statue.[r]
Out of breath, her eyes filled with tears.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

