[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Hey," Yuu breathed out, grinning like a dork.[l][r]
"... What?"[r]
My grumpy tone slowly returned to me; like second nature.[l][r]
Relief washed over Yuu as her expression softened, and the warmth she felt was overwhelming; like she just ate the tastiest thing in the world.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"... Why are you here? Are you a ghost?" Yuu tilted her head.[l][r]
"Is that really the first thing you say to me?" I crossed my arms.[l][r]
"W—Well, hey! You died, didn't you?"[r]
"... I guess I did."[r]
"So you couldn't even remember that you died?"[l][r]
"No, it's not like that... I couldn't tell if I was dead or not."[r]
"You were totally dead. Like, dead dead! Like that fish we ate!"[l][r]
"Don't compare me to a fish! And stop saying 'dead' all the time.." I scowled.[l][r]
"You said it more than I did," Yuu laughed, teasing me.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

